# pulse-rpc-node environment options
# Copy to .env (install.sh does this automatically):  cp .env.example .env
#
# v1 keeps defaults simple. These are reserved for optional tweaks / future use.
# docker-compose.yml currently uses hardcoded mainnet defaults for reliability.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Suggested validator fee recipient (when you later run a validator)
# Use a wallet address YOU control. Leave blank if you only need a private RPC.
# FEE_RECIPIENT=0xYourPulseChainAddressHere
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Optional: override data directory on the host (default matches official docs)
# Host layout: $DATA_DIR/jwt.hex, $DATA_DIR/execution, $DATA_DIR/consensus
# DATA_DIR=/blockchain

# Optional: HTTP RPC port (default 8545)
# HTTP_PORT=8545

# Optional: WebSocket RPC port (default 8546)
# WS_PORT=8546

# Optional: Beacon HTTP API port (default 3500)
# BEACON_HTTP_PORT=3500
